      • Table.ColumnMetaDatum

        private Table.ColumnMetaDatum(java.lang.String columnName,
                     int dataType,
                     int nullable,
                     java.lang.Integer charOctetLength)
                       throws se.miun.itm.input.model.InPUTException
        Constructs a ColumnMetaDatum that describes a column with the specified characteristics.
        Parameters:
        columnName - The name of the column.
        dataType - The type of data that the columns contains, which must be defined in the class Types.
        nullable - Either DatabaseMetaData.columnNullable or DatabaseMetaData.columnNoNulls, depending on whether the column allows NULL values.
        charOctetLength - If the type of data that the column contains is a character type, this is the maximum number of octets per datum in the column. Otherwise, it's ignored.
        Throws:
        se.miun.itm.input.model.InPUTException - If the specified data type isn't one of the types defined in the class java.sql.Types, or if the argument nullable isn't DatabaseMetaData.columnNullable or DatabaseMetaData.columnNoNulls.
